Chuying Agro Plans 4 Billion Yuan Organic Pig Complex, SCMP Says

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-03-20T20:50:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-20/chuying-agro-plans-4-billion-yuan-organic-pig-complex-scmp-says.html
Henan Chuying Agro-pastoral Co.
plans to spend 4 billion yuan ($609 million) setting up a
400,000-hectare organic pig farm in Henan province, the  South
China Morning Post  said, citing Director Wu Yide.  The project, to be completed in five years, will include a
feed plant, farms and a pork processing plant, the Hong Kong-
based English-language newspaper reported today.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  